			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Maybe this isn't important, but why increment the frame before loading the pointer? Won't that skip the first frame?</div><br />It would assuming you started the animation at zero. (A way to avoid this would be to set counter to 255 rather than 0 to start an animation.) I thought yours did the same, but you were inx-ing to skip the frame count, I guess.<br /><br />Edit: As for why, it avoids multiple loads of counter.</div>

					
